 outings - once a year - but it's not always - always - never any further than Epping Forest. There used to be the jaunt down there somewhere in Epping Forest and - more or - more or less of a - a - picnic do and - take your glass - take a - take a jar or
 old tin can to catch your tiddlers out the - out the pond. Yes. Time you got 'em home they were dead.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6173087 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8660755\charrsid5717858 How would you travel, would you go by train or bus or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2701361 WN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8660755\charrsid5717858 
Chara - chara. And - horse - horse bys. Down the old - down - weight off, you'd hav
e four or five - horse - horse driven coaches you know, and away you'd go, about a hundred of you, about twenty to the coach I suppose, or as many as they could get on. Some - some sitting on the steps. Which - used to cost you I think - used to cost a ha
'penny or a - ha'penny or a penny a week - towards the - towards the bun and - the balance of the outfit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6173087 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8660755\charrsid5717858 Would that be in the summer?
