I never had a holiday with me parents, couldn't afford it. The only time - I got a holiday was - childrens Country Holiday Fund and you started saving for that just after Chr
istmas, at a penny or tuppence or whatever you could afford a week, and - after you - you got five or six - after you got a - about five - five or six bob then - you went away for a fortnight's holiday down in - whatever part of the country that - not too
 
far out - where people - who were in the movement accepted you for - boarders, farms generally, farmers, because you could take part in the - doing something useful, occupying your time of the day, but it was - nearly always in the - in the season when - 
i
n - in the times when the farmers - really - could do - could do - could - could house you but not sort of get in their way like, even the fruit picking season, they didn't want you there in the fruit picking season. They didn't want you there in the hop 
picking season because their own - had their own crowds - regular crowds of East Enders coming down to do that, or Londoners, mostly East Enders or South - or from - people from over the water.
