No memory of it as a child. Of course I've got memories of it when I went down, we - we used to
 go down and - when we got a little older, round about the - 'course the first world war put a - put a block. I was only then coming fourteen, when the first world war - happened. And - that put the - the - that ruined the - young part of your life for th
e
 next five years, I mean - the age that - you should be doing something and seeing something was just dormant. Well 'course I - I followed me leader and then - I joined up under age in 17. Into the - the old 6th of London, 6th of London Rifles. I joined u
p.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6173087 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8660755\charrsid5717858 So you went hopping before the first world war?
